      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/167/5707",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو اَلْحَسَنِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"فِي اَلْمَفْقُودِ يُتَرَبَّصُ بِمَالِهِ أَرْبَعُ سِنِينَ ثُمَّ يُقْسَمُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5707 - Yunus ibn Abd Al-Rahman narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar who said that Abu Al-Hasan (as) said:\n\"In the case of a missing person (mafqud), his wealth is withheld for four years, and then it is divided.\""
        ]
      }
